track.name: No Way Back
comments: my first crack at real rock and i was instantly in love!
A bit too loud for me

When it first came out this song was a massive help in overcoming a bad bout of depression I was going through. It may not be the intended message, but to me, the song was saying something like: "Hey, fuck it, don't dwell on the past. You can't go back. But there's always a tomorrow. So let's go kick some ass!" I still get pumped listening to it to this day.
Although its a tough choice, would have to say this album is my favourite of theirs. Its dynamic, an emotional rollercoaster ride of rock n roll fun and thoughtful lyrics. Great stuff!!!
